description: Dassault Systemes CATIA (which stands for Computer-aided Three-dimensional Interactive Application) is an application that mechanical designers and engineers use to create and test tools, structures, machines, and machine components. CATIA is used in the aerospace, defense, architectural, and industrial machining industries, among others.
Versions 4 and below of CATIA save the 3D models users create as MODEL files. Version 5 saves users' models as PART files.
